=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: N-alkylate 5-bromopyridin-2(1H)-one with 2-bromoethanol (K2CO3/DMF) to give 5-bromo-1-(2-hydroxyethyl)pyridin-2-one. | Step 2: Miyaura borylation of this bromide (B2pin2, Pd catalyst) to the corresponding 5-boronate, 1-(2-hydroxyethyl)-2-oxo-1,2-dihydropyridin-5-yl-Bpin. | Step 3: Protect 2-amino-4-methyl-6-bromopyridine as the Boc carbamate, then Suzuki couple with the pyridone boronate to give BocNH–(4-methyl-6-(1-(2-hydroxyethyl)-2-oxopyridin-5-yl)pyridine) biaryl intermediate. | Step 4: Remove Boc to furnish the free aniline-type intermediate Cc1ccc(N)nc1-c1ccn(CCO)c(=O)c1. | Step 5: Convert 1-(2,2-difluorobenzo[d][1,3]dioxol-5-yl)cyclopropane-1-carboxylic acid to its acid chloride (SOCl2 or oxalyl chloride), then acylate the Step 4 amine to give the target Cc1ccc(NC(=O)C2(c3ccc4c(c3)OC(F)(F)O4)CC2)nc1-c1ccn(CCO)c(=O)c1.

